<br>
Let the word be spread that starting this day, March 15th in the springtime in the lands of Norrath that the Arrows of Light shall commence a full expression of their Norrathian heritage.  This event shall continue until mid-September, in the waning days of the Norrathian summer when we shall cease our event.<br>
<br>
/ooc - we are going to be roleplaying for a week, from Sunday (11/1) to Sunday (11/<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  of this week.  Check out your characters' dieties, race, hometown, class, and play it up!  Many people have never seen a roleplay event, or gotten the chance to hear extended chatter done in extended roleplay, so we are going to give it a try.<br>
<br>
/ooc - Ddont worry about being 'perfect' with this, there is no test at the end.  Just give it your best shot.  This is just a first-time run through to see how people like it and to add a little spice to the game.  There are some who /rp quite often, such as Tjohn, son of Tark (that name says roleplay all in itself!), and for those old enough to remember Bangoo, who did nothing BUT /rp, all the time!  (Remembers the distinctive barbarian drawl Bangoo would utter about ale, dancin' and M'ladies).<br>
<br>
/ooc If you want to say something not in roleplay, use the &quot;*ooc&quot; -- don't forget to put a symbol or space or * or whatever (anything but a &quot;/&quot;) so that it doesn't go zone-wide.<br>
<br>
/ooc Finally, drop the racial tensions.  We all know that iksars are hated by most races, and troll and ogres probably don't get along with froglocks and other tender races that go good in stew, but we don't want to create animosity within the guild.  Those in our guild are proven friends, despite their race, and as such, be treated as trusted friends (That's not to say that those froglocks can't hold a grudge against them *Frooaaaak* evil trolls up in Neriak, and Ogres can't compliment on da tasinesses of dem liddle halflings dat go gud in a soop).  Use your imagination. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Aevetare<br>
